Route guards means: before opening a page, app checks who is logged in.

Example:

Customer can open customer pages.
Charity can open charity pages.
Admin can open admin pages.
If wrong role, page does not open and user is redirected (like to login or home).
Centralized token-expiry/error flow means:

Instead of handling API errors in every component separately, one common place handles them.
If token is expired (401/403):
auto logout
show message like “Session expired, please login again”
redirect to login
For other errors:
show clean toast popup (success/error/warning) consistently everywhere.
So Step 1 gives you:

better security (no unauthorized page access)
cleaner code (less repeated error code)
better UX (clear messages for users)
